{
  "name": "fs_replace",
  "description": "Replace sections in a file using SEARCH/REPLACE blocks for precise modifications. ## Parameters - `path`: File path relative to /Users/test - `diff`: SEARCH/REPLACE blocks defining changes ## Format <<<<<<< SEARCH [exact content to find] ======= [new content to replace with] >>>>>>> REPLACE ## Rules 1. SEARCH must match exactly (whitespace, indentation, line endings) 2. Each block replaces first match only 3. Keep blocks minimal - include only changing lines plus needed context 4. Complete lines only - no truncation 5. For moves: use 2 blocks (delete + insert) 6. For deletes: use empty REPLACE section ## Example <<<<<<< SEARCH def old_function(x):     return x + 1 ======= def new_function(x, y=0):     return x + y >>>>>>> REPLACE",
